wwpLeosIpInterfaceMIB.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceMIB

revisions.description: The MIB module for the WWP IpInterface IP interfaces configuration. This MIB provide additional configuration to whatever is provided by the standard ip group.
A new object for management packet priority is added.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosIpInterfaceMIB.description: Added the operational gateway and a trap for gateway changes

VlanId.name: VlanId
VlanId.description: A 12-bit VLAN ID used in the VLAN Tag header.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceTable.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceTable
wwpLeosIpInterfaceTable.description: Table of IP addresses and associated subnet mask.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceEntry.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceEntry
wwpLeosIpInterfaceEntry.description: Interface IP and subnet mask entry. These interfaces are used to cause the switch CPU to become involved with the IP traffic. By default, a minimum of two interfaces must always exist, one for the local management interface, one for the remote management interface, and one or more for voice over IP.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceName.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceName
wwpLeosIpInterfaceName.description: The friendly name for the IP interface.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceIpAddr.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceIpAddr
wwpLeosIpInterfaceIpAddr.description: IP address associated with this interface.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceSubnet.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceSubnet
wwpLeosIpInterfaceSubnet.description: The subnet mask associated with this ip address/interface.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceIfIndexXref.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceIfIndexXref
wwpLeosIpInterfaceIfIndexXref.description: Cross reference to MIB-2 Interfaces ifIndex.

wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceTable.name: wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceTable
wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceTable.description: A table that contains Interface Specific information maintained by each interface.

wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceEntry.name: wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceEntry
wwpLeosIpExtInterfaceEntry.description: A list of interfaces additional configuration parameters maintained by each interface.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceEnable.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceEnable
wwpLeosIpInterfaceEnable.description: The status of each interface. A value of true(1) indicates that this interface is enabled and a value of false(2) indicates that this interface is disabled. The device shouldn't allow the Management Station to disable all the interfaces available on the box.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceVlanId.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceVlanId
wwpLeosIpInterfaceVlanId.description: The vlanId associated with this IP interface. The vlan indicated by wwpLeosIpInterfaceVlanId should exist in the Vlan Table. If an interface has no VLAN associated, then any read on this object should return 'noSuchInstance'.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority
wwpLeosIpInterfaceMgmtPktPriority.description: The 802.1p Priority value for the management traffic on this interface.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled
wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrNotifEnabled.description: This variable indicates whether the system generates the wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification. A false value prevents this notifications from being generated by this system.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification
wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification.description: A wwpLeosIpInterfaceAddrChgNotification is sent whenever the ip address of an interface changes.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceTable.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceTable
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceTable.description: Data Interface IP and subnet mask entry. To create a loopback interface in this table, following attributes must be specified. wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIndex wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceName wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIpAddr wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceType must be set to 'loopback'. wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceVlanId defaults to 1 and cannot be set or changed. No other MIB object should be set otherwise error will be returned. To create a regular Data interface the following attributes must be specified. wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIndex wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceName wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIpAddr wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMask wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceVlanId must be specified when the interface is created. It cannot be changed after creation. wwpLeosIpDataRowStatus must be set to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceEntry.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceEntry
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceEntry.description: Each entry represents a Data interface configuration parameter.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceName.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceName
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceName.description: The name for this Data IP interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIpAddr.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIpAddr
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIpAddr.description: IP address associated with this interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMask.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMask
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMask.description: The subnet mask associated with this ip address/interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceVlanId.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceVlanId
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceVlanId.description: The vlanId associated with this Data IP interface. This vlan must already exist on the device. The vlanId must be specified when the interface is created. It cannot be set after creation. The vlanId cannot be specified and defaults to 1 for a loopback interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceType.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceType
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceType.description: The type of Data IP interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfIndex.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfIndex
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfIndex.description: The unique interface index assigned by INET.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMac.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMac
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceMac.description: MAC address assigned by the device to this Data interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfMtu.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfMtu
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceIfMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets. For interfaces that are used for transmitting network datagrams, this is the size of the largest network datagram that can be sent on the interface.

wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceRowStatus.name: wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceRowStatus
wwpLeosIpDataInterfaceRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'destroy'. If the entry exists, it will be displayed as 'active'.

wwpLeosIpInterfaceOperationalGatewayChgN.name: wwpLeosIpInterfaceOperationalGatewayChgNotification
wwpLeosIpInterfaceOperationalGatewayChgN.description: A wwpLeosIpOperationalGatewayChgNotification notification will be sent out whenever the operational gateway is changed.

wwpLeosIpAclState.name: wwpLeosIpAclState
wwpLeosIpAclState.description: This object allows to globally configure IP ACL state.

wwpLeosIpAclCacheHit.name: wwpLeosIpAclCacheHit
wwpLeosIpAclCacheHit.description: Count of the number of lookups satisfied by a cache hit.

wwpLeosIpAclNoHit.name: wwpLeosIpAclNoHit
wwpLeosIpAclNoHit.description: Count of the number of lookups which failed because the source ip address did not match a table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclBadPort.name: wwpLeosIpAclBadPort
wwpLeosIpAclBadPort.description: Count of the number of lookups which failed because the ingress port was disallowed by a table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclClearStats.name: wwpLeosIpAclClearStats
wwpLeosIpAclClearStats.description: Set this object to 'destroy' to clear the global and table entry statistics counters.

wwpLeosIpAclBadDscp.name: wwpLeosIpAclBadDscp
wwpLeosIpAclBadDscp.description: Count of the number of lookups which failed because the ingress DSCP value was disallowed by a table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclOperState.name: wwpLeosIpAclOperState
wwpLeosIpAclOperState.description: The current operational state of the IP ACL system.

wwpLeosIpAclInUseEntries.name: wwpLeosIpAclInUseEntries
wwpLeosIpAclInUseEntries.description: Count of the number of IP ACL rules that are currently configured.

wwpLeosIpAclMaxEntries.name: wwpLeosIpAclMaxEntries
wwpLeosIpAclMaxEntries.description: Count of the max number of IP ACL rules that can be configured.

wwpLeosIpAclTable.name: wwpLeosIpAclTable
wwpLeosIpAclTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing the display parameters for the IP ACL table.

wwpLeosIpAclEntry.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntry
wwpLeosIpAclEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosIpAclTable.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpAddr.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpAddr
wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpAddr.description: This object is the IP network which will be authorized.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpMask.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpMask
wwpLeosIpAclEntryIpMask.description: This object is the netmask for the IP network which will be authorized.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortMask.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortMask
wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortMask.description: This object is used to specify the physical ports which frames will be allowed to ingress from. The mask is big endian and each bit, numbered from 0 to 27, represents a physical port numbered from 1 to 28. A value of 0xFFFFFFFF may be used to specify all ports.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryHits.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryHits
wwpLeosIpAclEntryHits.description: Count of the number of lookups which matched the table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadPort.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadPort
wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadPort.description: Count of the number of lookups which failed because the ingress port was disallowed by the table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryStatus.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryStatus
wwpLeosIpAclEntryStatus.description: Set this object to 'CreateAndGo' to create a new table entry, set it to 'destroy' to remove an existing entry.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryDscpMask.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryDscpMask
wwpLeosIpAclEntryDscpMask.description: This object is used to specify the DSCP values for which IP packets will be allowed to ingress. The mask is big endian and each bit, numbered from 0 to 63, represents a DSCP value numbered from 0 to 63. A value of 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF may be used to specify all.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadDscp.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadDscp
wwpLeosIpAclEntryBadDscp.description: Count of the number of lookups which failed because the ingress DSCP value was disallowed by the table entry.

wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortBitMask.name: wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortBitMask
wwpLeosIpAclEntryPortBitMask.description: This object is used to specify the physical ports which frames will be allowed to ingress from. The mask is big endian and each bit, numbered from 0 to 63, represents a physical port numbered from 1 to 64. A value of 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF may be used to specify all ports.
